  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \"Network request failed\" dialog is useful to let user know that some request has timed out because of a network issue. But, the dialog has started appearing every time a new screen is opened or message sent which makes it really annoying.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe dialog appears only when there was a network timeout while executing some request.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe dialog appears when you switch tabs (like Chats -> Wallet), open a chat or open any other screen. Even when sending a message.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/37960419-e5f47eee-31b5-11e8-8f7b-df63f4b7d3ac.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go offline (make sure to turn off wifi)\r\n- Go to chats sreens\r\n- Go to wallet screens\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, March 27\r\n* Works in 0.9.15\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
